# HW_01: Hello World

## Objective
Learn basic C++ program structure, compilation, and output.

## Requirements
Create a simple "Hello World" program that:

1. Prints "Hello, World!" to the console
2. Prompts the user for their name
3. Greets the user by name
4. Displays the current date (bonus: use system time)

## Example Output
Hello, World!
What is your name? John
Hello, John! Welcome to CSCI 330!
Today's date: [current date]

## Building and Testing

```bash
# Create build directory
mkdir build && cd build

# Configure
cmake ..

# Build
make

# Run tests
ctest --verbose

# Run your program
./src/hello_world
Submission

Work in branch HW_01
Commit frequently with meaningful messages
Push to your repository
Submit repository URL to Canvas

Due Date
[9/7/25]
Rubric

Program compiles without warnings (25%)
Correct output format (50%)
Code style and comments (25%)


**`HW_01/CMakeLists.txt`:**
```cmake
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.16)
project(HW_01 VERSION 1.0)

# Set C++ standard
set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)
set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD_REQUIRED ON)

# Compiler flags for better error detection
set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS} -Wall -Wextra -Werror")

# Enable testing
enable_testing()

# Add subdirectories
add_subdirectory(src)
add_subdirectory(tests)